{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Psychic|type2=Fairy}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Ralts}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Psychic|prevnum=279|prev=Pelipper|nextnum=281|next=Kirlia|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Ralts}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Ralts\n|jname=ラルトス\n|jtranslit=Rarutosu\n|tmname=Ralts\n|ndex=280\n|hdex=029\n|sdex=157\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=064\n|fbrow=026\n|abrow=157\n|obrow=133\n|opbrow=192\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Psychic\n|type2=Fairy\n|category=Feeling\n|height-ftin=1\'04"\n|height-m=0.4\n|weight-lbs=14.6\n|weight-kg=6.6\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Synchronize\n|ability2=Trace\n|abilityd=Telepathy\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Amorphous\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=1\n|evsa=1\n|expyield=40\n|oldexp=70\n|lv100exp=1,250,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=White\n|catchrate=235\n|body=12\n|pokefordex=ralts\n|generation=3\n|friendship=35\n}}\n\'\'\'Ralts\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ラルトス\'\'\' \'\'Ralts\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Psychic|Fairy}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation III]]. Prior to Generation VI, it was a pure {{type|Psychic}} Pokémon.\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Kirlia}} starting at [[level]] 20, which evolves into {{p|Gardevoir}} starting at level 30 or, if male, {{p|Gallade}} when exposed to a [[Dawn Stone]].\n\n==Biology==\n[[File:Raltseyes.png|thumb|left|90px|Ralts\'s eyes seen from below]]\nRalts is a humanoid Pokémon with a white body. It has thin arms and legs that widen toward the feet. There is a wispy extension trailing off the back of its feet, creating the overall impression of a nightgown or oversized dress. Most of its face is covered by green hair that resembles a {{wp|bowl cut}}, but a pair of pinkish red eyes is sometimes visible. There are two flat, red horns on top of its head: a large one toward the front and a smaller one at the back.\n\nRalts uses the horns to read people and Pokémon\'s emotions. Warm feelings cause its body to warm as well, but it hides if it senses hostility. If its {{pkmn|Trainer}} is in a cheerful mood, Ralts also becomes cheerful and joyous. It is known to inhabit {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Urban Pokémon|urban areas}}, but it does not normally show itself to humans. However, when it senses happy feelings, it will approach people.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Max Ralts.png|left|220px|thumb|Ralts in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nRalts debuted in \'\'[[AG109|Do I Hear a Ralts?]]\'\'. [[Max]] found one that was very sick and decided to prove his abilities by taking responsibility for it. With the help of {{AP|Snorunt}}, he rushed it to the nearest [[Pokémon Center]]. He later promised to return for Ralts when he became eligible to be a {{pkmn|Trainer}}.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Ralts appeared in a fantasy in \'\'[[AG133|The Right Place and the Right Mime]]\'\'.\n\nA Ralts appeared in \'\'[[AG146|Fear Factor Phony]]\'\' as a resident of an abandoned mining colony.\n\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Ralts appeared in \'\'[[AG160|Harley Rides Again]]\'\'.\n\nA Ralts appeared in \'\'[[M16|Genesect and the Legend Awakened]]\'\' as a resident of [[Pokémon Hills]].\n\nA Ralts appeared in [[BWS01]].\n\nA Ralts appeared in \'\'[[XY005|A Blustery Santalune Gym Battle!]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Ralts appeared in a fantasy in \'\'[[XY009|Clemont\'s Got a Secret!]]\'\', when it was defeated along with its Trainer by [[Clembot]].\n\nA Ralts appeared in \'\'[[XY016|A Jolting Switcheroo!]]\'\'.\n\nA Ralts appeared in \'\'[[XY021|A PokéVision of Things to Come!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Ralts appeared in \'\'[[XY026|A Battle by Any Other Name!]]\'\'.\n\nA Ralts appeared in \'\'[[XY029|Heroes - Friends and Faux Alike!]]\'\'\n\nA Ralts appeared in \'\'[[XY092|Cloudy Fate, Bright Future!]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{tc|Psychic}}.\n\nA Ralts appeared in \'\'[[XY105|Party Dancecapades!]]\'\', under the ownership of a [[Pokémon Performer]] participating in [[Monsieur Pierre]]\'s dance party.\n\nA Ralts appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\' as a resident of the [[Nebel Plateau]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Ralts appeared in \'\'[[XY138|The First Day of the Rest of Your Life!]]\'\'.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Hoenn}}\n{{Animedexbody|AG109|Ralts|May\'s Pokédex|Ralts, the Feeling Pokémon. Ralts is the pre-evolved form of {{p|Kirlia}}. It can use the horns on its head to read human emotions. Ralts rarely shows itself to humans, but may occasionally approach when it senses positive or happy feelings.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Advanced Generation\'\'|Hoenn}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Rara Ralts.png|thumb|150px|Ralts in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Ash & Pikachu manga===\nA Ralts appeared in \'\'[[SP30|The Birth Of The Invincible Team, Max And Ralts!!]]\'\', where it was taken care of by [[Max]] like in the anime.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{main|Rara}}\n{{adv|Ruby}} owned a Ralts [[nickname]]d Rara, who first appeared in \'\'[[PS181|Creeping Past Cacnea]]\'\'. However, for most of the {{chap|Ruby & Sapphire}}, Rara is with {{adv|Wally}} after Ruby was lost in an earthquake that left him under [[Mr. Briney]]\'s care (where he learned of the beautiful {{p|Milotic}} that [[Feefee]] eventually evolved into). While training with Wally under [[Norman]]\'s command, Rara evolves into a {{p|Kirlia}} and is eventually returned to Ruby.\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Mangadexheader}}\n{{Mangadexbody|Pokémon Adventures|[[PS187]]|This Pokémon can pick up emotions with its horns. It hardly appears before people but it is attracted to positive emotions.{{tt|*|Chuang Yi\'s translation}}}}\n{{Mangadexfooter}}\n{{Mangadexheader}}\n{{Mangadexbody|Pokémon Adventures|[[PS187]]|Ralts senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This Pokémon rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.{{tt|*|VIZ Media}}}}\n{{Mangadexfooter}}\n\n===In the Pokémon Battle Frontier manga===\nA Ralts appeared in \'\'[[CBF1|Enta Arrives at the Battle Frontier!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Ruby-Sapphire manga===\nA Ralts appeared in \'\'[[PMRS08|Esper Clefairy!]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Ralts (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Psychic|type2=Fairy}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=III}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=III|reg1=Hoenn|num1=029|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ruby|t=FFF|entry=Ralts senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This Pokémon rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=Ralts has the ability to sense the emotions of people. If its trainer is in a cheerful mood, this Pokémon grows cheerful and joyous in the same way.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Emerald|t=FFF|entry=A Ralts has the power to sense the emotions of people and Pokémon with the horns on its head. It takes cover if it senses any hostility.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=FireRed|v2=LeafGreen|entry=It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokémon. It hides if it senses hostility.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|num1=157|label1={{gameabbrev4|Pt}}:|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Diamond|v2=Pearl|entry=It uses the horns on its head to sense human emotions. It is said to appear in front of cheerful people.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Platinum|entry=If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=HeartGold|v2=SoulSilver|entry=The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people’s emotions.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=V|reg1=Unova}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black|v2=White|t=FFF|entry=If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warm